<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1600 GMT, June 14 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO -- A strong earthquake measuring 5.6 on the open-ended
Richter scale jolted eastern Japan Sunday night, the
Meteorological Agency of Japan said.
</P>
<P>
There were no immediate reports of damage or casualties and no
tsunami or tidal waves warnings were issued.
</P>
<P>
The focus of the quake, which occurred around 10:17 p.m. (local
time), was about 50 kilometers under the Pacific Ocean off the
east coast of Chiba Prefecture, east of Tokyo, the agency said.
(Japan-Quake)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- An Israeli court Sunday convicted 23-year-old
Magret Harshefi of failing to prevent her friend Yigal Amir from
murdering former prime minister Yitzhak Rabin in November 1995.
</P>
<P>
The Tel Aviv Magistrate Court ruled that Harshefi knew about
the intention of Amir, a fellow law student at Bar-Illan
University, to assassinate Rabin, but did nothing to stop him.
</P>
<P>
The court stressed that the ruling was based on Harshefi's own
testimony, which was given on her free will. (Israel-Rabin-Woman)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA -- Ethiopia announced Sunday 10,990 Eritrean
soldiers were killed or wounded in three-day ground fighting from
June 9 to 11.
</P>
<P>
A news release issued here by the office of the Ethiopian
government spokesperson also said that during the three-day
fighting in Badme, Zala Ambesa and Bure, about 150 Eritrean
soldiers were captured and thousands of heavy and light armaments
captured.
</P>
<P>
The news release said that 5,414 Eritrean soldiers were killed
or wounded in the fighting on the Badme front during June 10 and
11, in which troops of Eritrea's 381st and 161st divisions
participated. (Ethiopia-Eritrea-Fighting)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BEIRUT -- Lebanese in the eastern province of Bekaa Sunday
began voting in the fourth and final round of the first municipal
and mayoral elections in 35 years.
</P>
<P>
The Lebanese army tightened the security measures in key
intersections and around polling stations in order to avoid riot
or violence related to the polls.
</P>
<P>
The polls started at 7:00 a.m. (4:00 a.m. GMT) and will close
at 5:00 p.m. (2:00 p.m. GMT) and counting of votes will be
finished late Monday. (Lebanon-Local Elections)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
NEW DELHI -- India termed the reference to Indo-Pakistan
disputes in the joint communique of the Group Eight countries as
coercive and intrusive, and regretted that the G-8 decided to
block fresh loans to India.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the External Affairs Ministry said Saturday
night that India can not consider any prescriptions which had the
effect of undermining its independent decision-making.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman complained that major industrialized countries
did not respond to India's "positive gesture" made in recent
weeks. (India-G-8 Communique) 
</P>
</TEXT>
