<HEADLINE> Hunt For Five Missing Scots Called off </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 14 (Xinhua) -- The search for the crew of a
Scottish fishing vessel missing off the coast of Denmark was
called off on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Five Scottish fishermen were feared dead after their trawler
Silvery Sea went down early Sunday after a collision with a German
ship Merkur off the Danish coast, rescue officials said.
</P>
<P>
Coastguards said the search was given up after five-and-half
hour search on the Esbjerg sea. There was no prospect of finding
any of the five men alive.
</P>
<P>
"An empty 12-man inflated liferaft and uninflated rubber dinghy
was spotted as well as oil on the surface of the water," said a
spokesman for Britain's maritime and coastguard authorities.
</P>
</TEXT>
