<HEADLINE> Japanese Disappointed By Defeat </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
TOULOUSE, June 14 (Xinhua) -- Japanese head coach Takeshi Okada
said he was disappointed about his team's 1-0 defeat to Argentina in
their first ever World Cup match.
</P>
<P>
"The defeat by just one goal, we can accept that as a fact of
life. But I really regret that we have ended up without any goals,
regardless of whether we won or lost." said Okada.
</P>
<P>
Okada said:"The players were positive and aggressive and I
really feel very disappointed that we couldn't score at all."
</P>
<P>
"We all know that Argentina are stronger than us but we always
think that we had a chance of winning or drawing," said Okada,
"(But) in the world cup, the result is all that matters. In that
sense we were unfortunate."
</P>
<P>
Okada's Argentine counterpart Daniel Passarella was happy with
the win.
</P>
<P>
"We are very satisfied because it is important to win the first
match and it is always difficult." Passarella said.
</P>
<P>
"I feel satisfied, but not completely, because we could have
improved some things." said Passarella.
</P>
<P>
Passarella said:"I think that the Japanese team have changed
their tactics from the qualifying round. Maybe they were not
offensive enough in this match." 
</P>
</TEXT>
