<HEADLINE> Kurdish Rebels Kill 4 Turkish Soldiers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, June 14 (Xinhua) -- Rebels of the outlawed Kurdish
Workers' Party (PKK) has killed four Turkish soldiers and wounded
seven others in southeastern province of Tunceli, the
semi-official Anatolia News Agency reported on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Tunceli Governor Mehmet Ali Turker was quoted as saying that
the soldiers were killed when a group of PKK rebels ambushed on
Friday a Rapid Deployment Force vehicle on its way to a
watch-spot, not far away from the city center of Tunceli.
</P>
<P>
The agency also reported that a group of PKK rebels attacked a
radio station in Semdinli town of Hakkari province bordering
neighboring Iran Friday night, killing one village guard and
injuring five others.
</P>
<P>
The PKK has been fighting a 14-year-old separatist war for
independence in eastern and southeastern Turkey, which has claimed
over 35,000 lives since August 1984. 
</P>
</TEXT>
