<HEADLINE> Iran Raps Israeli Activities in East Jerusalem </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, June 14 (Xinhua) -- Iran on Sunday condemned recent
Israeli settlement activities in the occupied East Jerusalem as a
desecration of Islamic holy places, the official news agency IRNA
reported.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Ministry spokesman Mahmoud Mohammadi accused "the
Zionist regime (Israel)" for ignoring international regulations to
begin digging up the holy places in Jerusalem in order to build a
new settlement.
</P>
<P>
On June 8, a group of religious Jewish students moved into two
buildings in the Silwan neighborhood located in the Muslim Quarter
of East Jerusalem and triggered clashes with Palestinian residents.
</P>
<P>
The buildings were reportedly purchased by a extremist Jewish
organization, which is engaged in taking over Arab houses and land
in East Jerusalem through purchases in an attempt to Judaize the
city. A new settlement has been planned on the site.
</P>
<P>
But Israeli Antiquities Authorities announced Saturday the
discovery of remains of a medieval wall at the site, near the
Herod's Gate. It said the settlement construction should be
delayed at least for several months pending archeological diggings.
</P>
<P>
Mohammadi said Israeli actions to expand settlements indicated
the "aggressive and expansionist nature of the Zionist regime and
its illegitimate practices in the occupied Palestine."
</P>
<P>
He said this was proof that Israel is "the cause of the tension
and instability in the region." He added that Iran strongly
opposes any actions to change the traditional appearance of
Jerusalem, the third holy Islamic sites, after Mecca and Medina in
Saudi Arabia.
</P>
<P>
Mohammadi urged the international community and Islamic states
to adopt measures to seriously deal with Israel over the issue,
warning that the absence of a serious response would "stimulate
the illegitimate greed of the Zionists in their unlawful wishes."
</P>
</TEXT>
