<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, June 14 (Xinhua) -- Italian presidential envoy
Rino Aerri arrived here Sunday to mediate in the Ethio-Eritrean
border crisis.
</P>
<P>
Diplomatic sources said here that the visiting Italian envoy
went immediately into a closed-door meeting with Ethiopian
leaders after his arrival here from Asmara, capital of the state
of Eritrea.
</P>
<P>
No statement was made here after the meeting between Aerri
and Ethiopia Premier Meles Zenawi.
</P>
<P>
According to a report from Asmara, Eritrean President Isaias
Afwerki told the Italian envoy earlier Sunday that Eritrea is
ready for face-to-face talks with Ethiopia to seek an end to
the border war with its neighbor.
</P>
<P>
Aerri arrived in Asmara Saturday evening.
</P>
<P>
The Italian envoy is reported to propose that both Ethiopia and
Eritrea de-escalate their conflict, cease all air strikes and
start negotiations to seek a peaceful solution to their border
conflict.
</P>
<P>
Addis announced Sunday to have killed or wounded more than
10,990 Eritrean soldiers in three-day ground fighting from June
9 to 11.
</P>
<P>
The border dispute between the two Horn of African countries
turned violent since May when either side accused the other of
invasion.
</P>
<P>
Their dispute centered on a rocky 400 square km triangle of
border land which both countries claim. 
