<HEADLINE> France Opposed to Sanctions against Pakistan: Envoy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 15 (Xinhua) -- The French Ambassador to
Pakistan, Yannick Gerard, said here Monday France was opposed to
the imposition of sanctions against Pakistan for its testing of
nuclear devices.
</P>
<P>
However, Gerard said it was very important that the world be
protected against the nuclear proliferation and it was for the
international community, particularly the big powers, to help
remove the conditions which impelled countries like Pakistan to go
nuclear even for the defense or settlement of outstanding issues.
</P>
<P>
According to a press release by the National Assembly
Secretariat, the French Envoy made the remarks during his talks
with Pakistan's Deputy Speaker of the National Assembly Jafar
Iqbal.
</P>
<P>
Gerard said that France was fully alive to the circumstances
which led Pakistan to undertake the recent nuclear tests and that
it was imperative for both India and Pakistan to settle their all
outstanding issues including the core issue of Kashmir peacefully
and through dialogue.
</P>
<P>
Iqbal said that all efforts initiated by Pakistan to have a
negotiated settlement of the core issue of Kashmir were frustrated
by India and it was after the inception of the new government in
India that Pakistan received serious threats from across the
border.
</P>
<P>
The Deputy Speaker highlighted the unfaltering demand of the
entire Pakistani nation to employ all possible options to ensure
security of the country and to live with dignity and honor as a
sovereign state in the sub-continent.
</P>
<P>
He reiterated the continuing stance of Pakistan for peace and
security and appealed to the international community,
particularly, the big powers to come forward and help resolve the
core issue of Kashmir according to the relevant U.N. resolutions
and help defuse tension in the region. 
</P>
