</P>
<P>
TOKYO -- The U.S. dollar jumped over two yen in Tokyo on
Monday, hitting 146 yen for the first time in almost eight years,
as Japan's weak economy continued to weigh down the country's
currency.
</P>
<P>
The dollar was quoted at 146.43-46 yen at 5 p.m. (local time),
up sharply from 144.63-66 yen at 9 a.m., and 144.15-25 yen late
Friday in New York.
</P>
<P>
During the day, the dollar hit a high of 146.58 yen, a level
last seen in Tokyo on August 22, 1990, when it went as high as
146.95 yen. (Tokyo-Dollar-Yenn)
</P>
