<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Japan's Current Account Surplus Keeps Rising in April </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, June 15 (Xinhua) -- Japan's current account surplus rose
10.3 percent in April over the same period last year to 1.17
trillion yen (8.1 billion U.S. dollars), marking the thirteenth
straight month of increase, the Japanese Finance Ministry said
Monday.
</P>
<P>
The rise in April, however, was the smallest in the past 13
months, signaling a slower rate of growth in the measurement and
this slow pace "is expected to remain in the months ahead,"
according to a Finance Ministry official.
</P>
<P>
The current account surplus increased because falling imports
outpaced the decline in exports, the ministry said.
</P>
<P>
Japan's exports fell for the first time in 33 months despite
the weakness of the yen against the U.S. dollar, but imports
declined more amid the stagnant economy, said the ministry.
</P>
<P>
Exports in April edged down 2.4 percent compared with the same
month of last year to 4.21 trillion yen (28.8 billion dollars),
while imports fell by 13.8 percent to 2.85 trillion yen (19.5
billion dollars), a double-digit drop for the third consecutive
month.
</P>
<P>
Japan's exports to the United States and the European Union in
April marked a year-on-year expansion of 7.3 percent and 18.0
percent expansion respectively, but those to Asian countries fell
by 18.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
In goods and services trade, Japan posted a surplus of 726.3
billion yen (4.9 billion dollars), up 83.6 percent from a year
earlier.
</P>
<P>
The surplus in merchandise trade grew 35 percent to 1.36
trillion yen (9.3 billion dollars), up for the thirteenth
consecutive month, the ministry said.
</P>
<P>
In services trade, Japan posted a deficit of 632.4 billion yen
(4.3 billion dollars), up from a deficit of 610.5 billion yen (4.2
billion dollars) a year earlier.
</P>
<P>
The current account measures the flow of goods and services, as
well as investment income and other monetary transfers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980615.0044 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-15 </DATE_TIME>
