<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Workers Enjoy Steady Income Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 15 (Xinhua) -- Chinese workers' annual incomes
averaged 6,470 yuan (about 855 US dollars) in 1997, up 1.1 percent
on a year-by-year basis, according to a report released here today
jointly by the State Statistics Bureau and the Ministry of Labor
and Social Security.
</P>
<P>
Wages for workers in urban areas last year climbed by 3.6
percent, while those for employees of state enterprises rose by
6.2 percent, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The social labor productivity calculated in gross domestic
product (GDP) was 10,800 yuan (about 1,350 US dollars), or 7.5
percent higher than in the previous year, with inflation deducted.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, over 86 million workers and 25 million
retired workers across the country were included in old age
pension programs, while 35 million had joined insurance schemes
for industrial accidents by the end of 1997.
</P>
<P>
Altogether, 79.61 million people joined unemployment insurance
schemes, among whom 3.19 million received unemployment relief
funds.
</P>
<P>
The report said the number of workers involved in medical care
insurance programs had reached 11 million by the end of last year,
while that with maternity insurance was 24 million.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
