<HEADLINE> Wuhan, Bordeaux Become Sister Cities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, June 15 (Xinhua) -- This capital of central China's
Hubei Province, has established a sister-city relationship with
France's Bordeaux.
</P>
<P>
Alain Juppe, former prime minister of France and mayor of
Bordeaux, and Wang Shouhai, mayor of Wuhan, signed an agreement to
this effect Sunday evening.
</P>
<P>
According to the agreement, the two cities will conduct
exchanges and cooperation in economic and trade, scientific,
educational and cultural areas.
</P>
<P>
Bordeaux, a major harbor and aviation hub in southwest France,
is advanced in the telecommunications and chemical industries.
</P>
<P>
Prior to the signing ceremony, the two mayors exchanged views
on establishing a French Industrial Park in Wuhan.
</P>
<P>
Already 22 Sino-French joint ventures have been set up in
Wuhan, with a total contractual investment of 1.46 billion US
dollars.  
</P>
