<HEADLINE> Spanish Wines Enjoy Growing Popularity in Asia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 15 (Xinhua) -- Total exports of wines and
spirits from Spain to Asia reached over 41 million U.S. dollars in
1997, jumping 91 percent over the previous year, the Spanish Trade
Commission said here Monday.
</P>
<P>
Of this wine trade, 28 percent or 12 million U.S. dollars were
due to Spanish exports to China's inland areas, a 400 percent
increase over the previous year, while Spain's 1997 exports of
alcoholic beverages to Hong Kong soared a dramatic 584 percent to
5.7 million U.S. dollars, said Ernesto Tejedor, Spain's Trade
Commissioner in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
To further promote Spanish wines and spirits in the Asia
market, the Spanish Trade Commission and the Spanish Institute for
Foreign Trade (ICEX) have organized a Spanish Pavilion of 56
exhibitors at V&AMP;S Hong Kong '98, the first international wine and
spirits exhibition for the Asia Pacific taking place in Hong Kong
from June 16 to 18.
</P>
<P>
Over 38 different Spanish fine wines and spirits will feature
in the Spanish Pavilion, said Paloma Escorihuela Esteban, head of
ICEX's Wine Department.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong is Spain's second largest export market in Asia. In
1997, total exports from Spain to Hong Kong amounted to over 614
million U.S. dollars, of which around 50 percent were re-exported
to the Chinese mainland. 
</P>
</TEXT>
