<HEADLINE> Asia's Most Advanced Treasury Dealing Room Opened in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 15 (Xinhua) -- Standard Chartered Bank, one of
the three note-issuing banks in Hong Kong, opened Asia's most
advanced dealing room here Monday.
</P>
<P>
Seventy million HK dollars (8.97 million U.S. dollars) was
invested in the dealing room, which has space for 100 dealing
workstations, according to Stanley Wong, the bank's regional
treasurer for Northeast Asia.
</P>
<P>
The main feature of the dealing room, located on the seventh
floor of the bank's Hong Kong headquarters in Central, is the 300
state-of-the-art flat-screen displays that are linked to 100
personal computers on another floor in the building, Wong said.
</P>
<P>
The main benefits are flexibility and speed -- dealers can
operate fully from any dealing position in the room and can react
at a moment's notice to changing market conditions, he said.
</P>
<P>
The bank's Group Chairman Patrick Gillam, who also officiated
at the opening ceremony, said the dealing room indicated the
international banking group's long commitment to Hong Kong. The
British-funded group has operated in Hong Kong for around 140
years.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong is the most profitable of Standard Chartered Global
Treasury's network of 28 dealing rooms around the world. Last
year the bank's treasury operations in Hong Kong achieved a 45
percent increase in profits. 
</P>
</TEXT>
