<HEADLINE> Christie's to Inaugurate Sale of Fine and Rare Wines in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 15 (Xinhua) -- Christie's will hold its
inaugural sale of fine and rare wines here Thursday as part of the
international wine and spirits exhibition (V&AMP;S de Vinexpo) to be
held between Tuesday and Thursday at the Hong Kong Convention and
Exhibition Center.
</P>
<P>
Expected to realize over six million HK dollars (769,231 U.S.
dollars), the exceptional sale offers a rare opportunity for
collectors to acquire quality wines at auction in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Duncan McEuen, director of Christie's London Wine Department,
said Monday at a press briefing that following a long tradition of
holding a Fine Wine Auction at the biannual Vinexpo in Bordeaux,
Christie's is delighted to have been invited by the V&AMP;S de Vinexpo
to mount a similar event at their inaugural wine fair in the
Asia-Pacific region.
</P>
<P>
"It is a particular pleasure to be able to take a superb
quality sale direct to the center of the rapidly expanding and
highly enthusiastic wine market that is now becoming established
in Asia-Pacific," McEuen said.
</P>
<P>
Highlights of the sale include 12 bottles of Chateau
Cheval-Blanc 1947, a superb jeroboam of the very rare Le Pin 1982,
cases of Chateau Petrus 1990, individual bottles of the same wine
of the legendary 1961 vintage and Chateau Mouton Rothschild 1945.
</P>
<P>
Of particular interest to the Asian market are a number of
wines from Spain, Italy, Australia and California, USA.
</P>
<P>
Most notable among them are L'Ermita 1994 and Vega Sicilia from
Spain, of which five vintages are offered dating back to 1953,
Astralis 1996 and four vintages of Grange back to 1972 from
Australia, and Sassicaia 1990 from Italy. 
</P>
