<HEADLINE> China to Launch Fourth Securities Investment Fund </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 15 (Xinhua) -- China will launch its fourth
securities investment fund tomorrow, in another move to develop
institutional investors in the securities market.
</P>
<P>
The "Anxin Fund", which is also the first investment fund run
by a local fund manager, is expected to be issued at 1.01 yuan per
unit.
</P>
<P>
The three sponsors, namely the Shanghai International Trust and
Investment Company, Shandong Securities Co. Ltd and Hua'an
Fund Management Co. Ltd, are expected to purchase 60 million units
of the fund, while the remaining 1.94 billion units will be
offered to the public through the Shanghai Stock Exchange.
</P>
<P>
The closed-end fund has a 15-year term, and will invest 70
percent of the capital in stocks and 30 percent in treasury
bonds. The Industrial and Commercial Bank of China will be the
custodian of the fund.
</P>
<P>
Market analysts say the introduction of the fourth securities
investment fund shows clearly the strong determination of the
securities authorities to standardize and stabilize the stock
market by encouraging institutional investors.
</P>
<P>
The first three such funds, namely the "Jintai Fund", "Kaiyuan
Fund" and "Xinghua Fund", have been warmly welcomed by investors
due to the security and profitability an investment fund
promises. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
