<HEADLINE> Six Die in Fujian Landslide </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, June 15 (Xinhua) -- Six people died and one is missing
in a landslide triggered by torrential rains that lashed the city
of Nanping in eastern China's Fujian Province from June 12 to 14.
</P>
<P>
The downpour flooded three counties around Nanping in northern
Fujian and brought the water levels in the rivers well above the
danger lines. It destroyed 1,355 ha of crops, washed away parts of
highways and seriously damaged water conservation facilities.
</P>
<P>
The Wuyishan Airport in the region was temporarily closed as
most of its runways were under water and some communications and
navigation facilities were paralysed by lightning.
</P>
<P>
Local sources said the direct property losses are estimated at
over 500 million yuan (about 62.5 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
The local government is organizing resue operations, and relief
supplies are on the way.  
</P>
