<HEADLINE> Two Lost in Cave Rescued After 42 Days </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUIYANG, June 15 (Xinhua) -- Two young girls have been rescued
alive after being lost in a cave for 42 days in southwest China's
Guizhou Province.
</P>
<P>
Doctors called it a miracle that the two girls, Li Qingzhu, 16,
and Liang Xiaofei, could survive by living only on water for such
a long time.
</P>
<P>
They were found two days ago, when four other people entered
the unnamed cave to explore it. Li was conscious, but Liang was
not. The girls' companions, Huang Yan and a boy named Wang
Shunrong, had died.
</P>
<P>
The four entered the cave May 2, not having informed anyone of
where they were going, and got lost when their candles went out.
</P>
<P>
Their schools reported them missing seven days later. 
</P>
