<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sino-Italian Joint Communique Issued </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 15 (Xinhua) -- China and Italy are determined to
develop an efficient and long-term bilateral relationship in all
fields on the basis of faithful partnership
</P>
<P>
This was stated in a Sino-Italian joint communique which was
issued at the end of Italian President Oscar Luigi Scalfaro's
state visit to China June 8-13.
</P>
<P>
Both countries promise to make concerted efforts to contribute
to the establishment of a new international political and economic
order featuring fairness and reasonableness, the communique said.
</P>
<P>
Since both countries bear important responsibilities in
regional and international affairs, the communique emphasized,
strengthened exchanges and cooperation between the two countries
in such global organizations as the United Nations not only
accords with their mutual interests, but is conducive to the
peace, stability and development of the world as a whole.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, both sides will devote themselves to establishing a
brand-new Asian-European partnership, through which both will
enhance their discussions and cooperation concerning world
affairs, while at the same time positively promoting China's
dialogue with the European Union.
</P>
<P>
Such key issues as United Nations affairs, security and
disarmament, proliferation of nuclear weapons and weapons of mass
destruction should be fully and frequently discussed, the
communique noted, adding that any crises threatening world
peace and stability should be promptly addressed.
</P>
<P>
As it is significant for leaders of the two countries to keep
in close and frequent touch, the communique said, both
sides decided to hold regular summit talks, as well as meetings
between the two foreign ministers at least once a year.
</P>
<P>
Bilateral economic and trade relations, hailed as an important
component of the Sino-Italian relationship, will be further
explored, especially in terms of bilateral trade, and industrial
and financial cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Both sides agreed that the role of the Sino-Italian Joint
Economic and Trade Committee should be strengthened in enhancing,
coordinating and supervising the functions of cooperative agencies
in the two countries, and in deciding on special fields to
cooperate in and putting forward concrete suggestions.
</P>
<P>
Exchanges and cooperation between medium- and small-sized
enterprises are encouraged, while further cooperation between
large ones continue, the communique noted.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
