<HEADLINE> Pakistan, Turkey Hold Talks on Defense Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 15 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan and Turkey began here
Monday their annual defense talks with an emphasis on
strengthening bilateral defense cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The talks took place at the forum of Pakistan-Turkey Defense
Consultative Group, which was established in 1995 and meets once a
year for enhancing the defense cooperation between the two
countries, said an official press release.
</P>
<P>
In Monday's opening session, the two sides expressed their
resolve to explore the possibilities to promote collaboration and
cooperation in the fields of defense production and military
training, the release said.
</P>
<P>
It said that various working groups would be formed later to
identify different areas for strengthening defense relations.
</P>
<P>
A 10-member Turkish defense delegation led by Lt. General
Tuncer Kilinicunder, secretary of the minister of national
defense, arrived here Sunday for the talks.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan's Defense Secretary Lt. General (R) Iftikhar Ali Khan
met Tuncer Kilinicunder earlier Monday and termed the relationship
between the two countries as special and unique, according to the
release.
</P>
<P>
Iftikhar said that Pakistan and Turkey shared common views and
perceptions on major issues and were committed to promoting peace
and human development.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, the two also discussed security issues and
pledged to work closely with each other, the release said.
</P>
