<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 40 Die in Hunan Floods </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, June 15 (Xinhua) -- The death toll from floods caused
by continuous torrential rains in central China's Hunan Province
has risen to 40, according to the local anti-flood department.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that more than four million people have been
affected by the floods, which have wreaked havoc in 16 counties
and destroyed more than 100,000 houses in central and northern
Hunan.
</P>
<P>
The torrential rain began in the evening of June 12, causing
river water to rise sharply over the danger level, and cutting off
communications, traffic and power supply in some areas, and even
forced some enterprises to stop production.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government has issued a circular calling on the
whole province to be on alert against floods.
</P>
<P>
A relief office has been set up by the provincial government to
coordinate the relief efforts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
