<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesian Attorney General Replaced </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, June 15 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian President B.J. Habibie
here Monday announced the replacement of the attorney general of
the country, a minister said.
</P>
<P>
According to a Presidential Decree, Attorney General Soedjono
C. Atmonegoro will be replaced by Maj. Gen. Andi Muhammad Galib,
said State Secretary/Minister Akbar Tanjung.
</P>
<P>
However, he did not disclose the details of the replacement,
but stressed that the move has no connection with the
investigation on the wealth of present and former government
officials, including former president Soeharto and his family.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this month, Soedjono told reporters that the Attorney
General's office has formed a team led by the Junior Attorney
General to investigate the wealth of government officials.
</P>
<P>
When the investigations are finished, "the result (of the
investigations) of officials of both central and provincial
governments will be announced to the public," said a spokesman of
the Attorney General's office. 
</P>
</TEXT>
