<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing to Host Auto China '98 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 15 (Xinhua) -- China's most prestigious
automotive exhibition is to be held here June 23-30.
</P>
<P>
More than 800 automotive enterprises from 23 countries and
regions worldwide will display their products at the Auto
China '98 exhibition, including almost every well-known auto
giant, such as GM, Ford, Daimler-Chrysler, Toyota, Honda,
Volkswagen, BMW and Fiat.
</P>
<P>
Foreign companies will send more than 130 vehicles to the
exhibition, including ones specially designed for the China market.
</P>
<P>
GM will introduce the Buick sedan car that its joint venture in
Shanghai will start to manufacture in October. Honda will display
the Accord model that its joint venture in south China's Guangzhou
will produce soon. Mercedes-Benz will display an E-class car
specially designed for Chinese buyers.
</P>
<P>
Environmentally safe automotives are the highlight of this
exhibition. AXcess Australia is expected to display a car with a
body weight of only 69 kg. Three of Ford's new cars burn
compressed natural gas, while the China Aerospace Corporation will
unveil a mixed-fuel automobile.
</P>
<P>
The products at the exhibition will represent the technological
standards and development trend in the world's automobile industry
not only in China but in the rest of the world.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition will also display parts and components,
manufacturing equipment, maintenance and inspection equipment and
other automobile-related products.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the exhibition will hold special sessions for people
from the media and the automobile industry from June 23 to 24. It
will also present special lectures and forums.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition organizers may be connected at
http:www.auto-china.org.  
</P>
</TEXT>
