<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Prosinecki Makes World Cup History </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 15 (Xinhua) -- Croatian midfielder Robert Prosinecki
made World Cup finals history Sunday night when he became the first
player to score goals for two countries.
</P>
<P>
Prosinecki represented Yugoslavia in the 1990 World Cup finals and
scored a goal against the United Arab Emirates at that edition.
</P>
<P>
In Sunday's 3-1 game against Jamaica, he netted for Croatia when he
lobbed a ball in over Jamaican goalkeeper Warren Barrett.
</P>
<P>
Prosinecki, who now plays with Croatian side Zagreb, won European
and Interncontinental Cup with Crvena Zvezda Belgrade in 1991.
</P>
<P>
He then served Real Madrid, Barcelona and Sevilla in Spain before
returning to Zagreb in 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
