<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guangdong Economy Fares Well </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, June 15 (Xinhua) -- South China's Guangdong Province
has achieved "a relatively good achievement that surpasses
expectations in economy," said Gao Siren, deputy secretary of the
provincial committee of the Chinese Communist Party today.
</P>
<P>
In a meeting with over 20 non-communist personalities, Gao said
that the achievement manifests in all areas of the economy, with
grain output for the spring season topping all records in history.
</P>
<P>
The province produced 1.059 million tons of grain, 78,000 tons
more than the same period last year, he said.
</P>
<P>
The provincial industry grew 12.4 percent during the past five
months, with their total output value reaching 336.56 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the province exported 29.77 billion US dollars, 19.2
percent more than the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The markets have also been active, with the provincial retail
sales volume rising by 12 percent to 128.78 billion yuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
