<HEADLINE> Belarussian President Starts Visit to Egypt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, June 15 (Xinhua) -- Belarussian President Alexandr
Lukashenko arrived here Monday on a two-day official visit to
Egypt for talks with his Egyptian counterpart Hosni Mubarak on
bilateral ties and other issues of mutual interest.
</P>
<P>
Upon his arrival at the Cairo International Airport, Lukashenko
was greeted by Mubarak and other senior Egyptian officials.
</P>
<P>
The talks between the two presidents are to focus on a number
of regional and international issues of mutual concern, the latest
developments in the Mideast peace process, as well as enhancing
bilateral ties, especially in economy, trade and investment,
according to media reports here.
</P>
<P>
They will sign a number of agreements on reactivating economic
and trade relations as well as encouraging foreign
investments. The two countries are also expected to sign a number
of other accords on preventing dual taxation and enhancing
bilateral cooperation in higher education.
</P>
<P>
Accompanied by a number of businessmen on his first trip to
Egypt, Lukashenko will meet with Egyptian businessmen to discuss
bilateral cooperation in boosting trade ties.
</P>
<P>
Belarus is the most developed of the Commonwealth of
Independent States in the field of industry.
</P>
<P>
Trade exchange between the two countries stood at 63 million
U.S. dollars last year, including 3 million dollars of Egyptian
exports to Belarus and 60 million dollars of Egyptian imports
from Belarus.
</P>
<P>
Belarussian Foreign Minister Ivan Antonovich visited Egypt in
January and signed two agreements on encouraging foreign
investments in the two countries and promoting bilateral economic
and technical relations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
