<HEADLINE> Singapore to Host 1st Asia International Book Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, June 15 (Xinhua) -- Singapore will host the first
Asia International Book Fair (AIBF) in the year of 2000, according
to a press release issued Monday by the Reed Exhibition Companies
(REC).
</P>
<P>
The event scheduled for April 26-28, 2000, at the Singapore
International Convention and Exhibition Center is co-organized by
REC, Singapore, and TDB Holding Pte. Ltd., an investment
subsidiary of the Singapore Trade Development Board, it said.
</P>
<P>
The REC claimed to be "the world's leading organizer of trade
and public shows with a current portfolio of 336 events servicing
52 industry sectors."
</P>
<P>
Under the AIBF scheme, the trading of books and publishing
rights will be brought under one roof to fill the gap in Asia's
publishing industry, REC said.
</P>
<P>
It also said that a conference will be held in conjunction with
the exhibition to provide an opportunity for exchange of ideas
between industry professionals and education policy makers.
</P>
<P>
Tham Hock Chee, director of business development at the
Singapore Trade Development Board, was quoted as saying that "the
AIBF will be a publishing rights trade fair where international
and regional publishers can gather to exchange ideas, view latest
technologies and conclude deals." 
</P>
</TEXT>
