<HEADLINE> Mandela to Visit Italy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, June 15 (Xinhua) -- South African President
Nelson Mandela will arrive in Italy Tuesday and meet his Italian
counterpart Oscar Luigi Scalfaro.
</P>
<P>
South African Foreign Affairs Department spokesman Marco Boni
made the announcement Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Boni said that President Mandela will also meet Italian Prime
Minister Romano Prodi during his stay in Italy.
</P>
<P>
Mandela's visit "will be an opportunity to consolidate the
growing economic links between South Africa and Italy", Boni
said.
</P>
<P>
Italy is one of South Africa's top five trading partners, with
two-way trade amounting to 1.6 billion U.S. Dollars last year.
</P>
</TEXT>
