<HEADLINE> Malaysia, Singapore to Conduct Joint Air Exercise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, June 15 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia and Singapore will
conduct a two-day air defense exercise codenamed "Minor Adex 98-3"
beginning Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
A Defense Ministry statement Monday said the exercise will be
held under the ambit of the Five Power Defense Arrangement (FPDA)
of which the two countries are members.
</P>
<P>
"The aim of Adex is to exercise the air defense forces of the
two regional member nations in preserving the integrity of their
airspace against a simulated external air threat," it said.
</P>
<P>
Adex will be coordinated by the Headquarters Integrated Air
Defense System located at the Royal Malaysian Air Force Base in
Butterworth about 370 kilometers from here.
</P>
<P>
The statement said some of the aircraft and air defense units
participating in the exercise are F5, F16, MiG 29, Hawks, C130,
ground-based air defense radar units, surface-to-air missiles and
anti-aircraft artillery.
</P>
<P>
Other members of the FPDA are Britain, Australia and New
Zealand. 
</P>
