<HEADLINE> Heavy Flooding in Eastern Jiangxi Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, June 15 (Xinhua) -- Successive days of heavy rainfall
has battered northeastern part of east China's Jiangxi Province,
inundating vast stretches of cultivated fields and besieging over
10,000 farmers.
</P>
<P>
Local hydrological stations report that the Xinjiang River, a
branch of the Poyang Lake on the Yangtze River, has surpassed the
danger level by close to four meters.
</P>
<P>
Local governments at all levels have sent rescue teams and
rushed relief supplies to victims in flood-stricken areas.
</P>
<P>
Shu Huiguo, secretary of the Jiangxi Provincial Committee of
the Communist Party of China (CPC), instructed concerned
departments to "adopt all possible means to ensure the safety and
property of local residents."
</P>
<P>
Northeastern Jiangxi, a major traffic hub linking central and
northern China, has a long history of flood control efforts.
</P>
<P>
Heavy rain which has hit the region since June 11 has
dramatically raised the water level on the Xinjiang River,
</P>
<P>
Leading officials in Shangrao and Yingtan, both of which
sustained heavy flooding, immediately visited flooded areas and
dispatched both trucks and boats. Sources noted that flood victims
will be moved to safe areas.
</P>
<P>
Weather forecasts are less than optimistic and rain is expected
to continue through June 20.  
</P>
</TEXT>
