<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, June 15 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed lower across the board Monday with
buyers shying away on continued uncertainty in the foreign
exchange market as the local currency -- the ringgit declined
further.
</P>
<P>
The weakening ringgit has prompted selling on bluechip shares
mainly by foreign funds.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stock Composite Index fell 20.13
points to 452.24, the all-share Emas Index slipped 4.18 points to
117.84, the Industrial Index dropped 34.85 points to 915.50 while
the Second Board index eased 2.20 points to 104.16.
</P>
<P>
Losers led gainers by 549 to 80, 124 counters were unchanged
and 189 counters were untraded.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover was 108.059 million shares valued at 232.654
million ringgit (57.163 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the main board eased to 102.272 million shares
worth 224.866 million ringgit (55.249 million dollars) from
113.470 million shares valued at 259.507 million ringgit (63.76
million dollars) last Friday.
</P>
<P>
On the Second Board, turnover fell to 5.787 million shares
valued at 7.787 million ringgit (1.912 million dollars) from 6.174
million shares worth at 8.699 million ringgit (2.137 million
dollars) last Friday.
</P>
<P>
