<DOCNO> XIE19980615.0132 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tree-planting Drive Starts in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, June 15 (Xinhua) -- A three-month long countrywide tree
planting drive began Monday in Bangladesh with an aim to enhance
tree-planting awareness among the people.
</P>
<P>
President Shahabuddin Ahmed and Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina
issued messages separately on the eve of the drive, calling upon
all to take part in the drive to save the country's environment.
</P>
<P>
"Large scale tree planting can meet the demands for shelter and
fodder of wild animals," Hasina said in her message.
</P>
<P>
She urged people to refrain from indiscriminate felling of
trees to save the country from environment degradation.
</P>
<P>
She also called for making optimum use of land by planting
trees on marginal lands, courtyards, pond borderlines, roadsides,
embankments and canals since Bangladesh is one of the most
densely-populated countries in the world.
</P>
<P>
A fortnight-long cultural program would also be held in the
capital city of Dhaka in observance of the drive.
</P>
<P>
The objective of organizing the grass root-level drive is to
achieve the goal of planting at least two trees -- one
fruit-bearing tree and one fine wood tree -- at every house
throughout the country with a population of 127 million living in
about 20 million households. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
