<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Croatia Players Happy with First Match Win </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
LENS, June 15 (Xinhua) -- The Croatian players were very happy
with their 3-1 win over Jamaica here last night.
</P>
<P>
Captain Zvonimir Boban said:"Obviously I'm very satisfied and very
happy with the result of the match. After so many warm-up matches,
it's great to win a match in the World Cup."
</P>
<P>
"We are not better than we were in Euro 96, just more
experienced. On the field my job is to motivate the team and I'm
ready to do that in all the remaining matches." said Boban.
</P>
<P>
Robert Jarni said:"Of course we were going for the win. We had
some difficulties in the first half, but then we calmed things down.
We are aiming for the quarter-finals, but we need to play to the
best of our ability and to have some good luck."
</P>
<P>
Striker Davor Suker said:"We played and won like favorites. We
created a lot of chances and the three goals we scored have boosted
our confidence."
</P>
<P>
Mario Stanic, who opened the scoring for Croatia, said:"It was
fantastic to score Croatia's first goal in the World Cup, even
though I'm hard put to explain how it happened. We played a good
opening game, but you will see an even stronger Croatia against
Japan. I am ready to play in any position for my country, even in
goal." 
</P>
</TEXT>
