<DOCNO> XIE19980615.0138 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bruneian Sultan Meets China's NPC Leader </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANDAR SERI BEGAWAN, June 14 (Xinhua) -- China and Brunei
Monday shared the view that further strengthening good neighborly
friendship between the two countries conforms to the fundamental
interests of the two peoples.
</P>
<P>
The view was expressed by Brunei's Sultan and Supreme Head of
State Haji Hassanal Bolkiah and visiting Vice Chairman of the
Standing Committee of the National People's Congress of China Xie
Fei during their meeting here Monday.
</P>
<P>
At the meeting, Xie Fei first conveyed Chinese President Jiang
Zemin's greetings and good wishes to the Bruneian Sultan and said
that during the current visit he was happy to see the achievements
made by Brunei under the leadership of the Sultan in various
fields.
</P>
<P>
Xie Fei said China will continue to adhere to the policy of
good neighborliness and friendship and will also actively promote
the mutually beneficial cooperation with neighboring countries
including Brunei.
</P>
<P>
Xie said that there exist great potentials for cooperation
between China and Brunei and both sides could learn from each
other for common development in many fields.
</P>
<P>
Agreeing with Xie's views on the bilateral relations, the
Brunei Sultan said his visit to China in 1993 left him deep
impressions and that various policies being pursued by China are
all correct.
</P>
<P>
The Sultan expressed the belief that under the leadership of
Jiang Zemin, China will be successful in achieving its objective
of modernization and will play a more important role on the
international forum.
</P>
<P>
He said the bilateral relations between Brunei and China are
very good and there exist no obstacles in the development of
cooperation between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
He pledged that Brunei will work towards further strengthening
the bilateral cooperation between the two countries especially in
the economic and trade field.
</P>
<P>
The Sultan requested Xie to convey his greetings and respects
to Jiang Zemin.
</P>
<P>
Xie Fei arrived here Sunday afternoon for a three-day official
visit to Brunei. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
