<HEADLINE> Brunei FM Meets China's NPC Leader </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANDAR SERI BEGAWAN, June 15 (Xinhua) -- Brunei Foreign
Minister Mohammed Bolkiah met here Monday with visiting Vice
Chairman of the Standing Committee of the National People's
Congress (NPC) of China Xie Fei and the two sides spoke highly of
the achievements made in the development of bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, the Brunei foreign minister praised China
for its important role in the international and regional affairs,
saying during the financial crisis, the commitment made by China
not to devaluing its currency Renminbi showed that China as a big
country is very responsible and Brunei is thankful to that.
</P>
<P>
Xie Fei briefed the Brunei foreign minister of China's efforts
in promote peace and development in the region and stressed that
China is consistently pursuing a foreign policy of
good-neighborliness.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that nations, big or small, are equal. He welcomed
Brunei to continue to make contributions to the development and
prosperity of the region.
</P>
<P>
The two sides also exchanged views on friendly cooperation in
the field of agriculture and other fields.
</P>
<P>
Xie Fei arrived here Sunday afternoon for a three-day official
visit to Brunei. 
