<HEADLINE> Share Prices Tumble on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, June 15 (Xinhua) -- Share prices tumbled on the
Singapore market as the benchmark Straits Times Industrials Index
(STII) lost 38.65 points to close at 1,053.84 points Monday.
</P>
<P>
Share prices closed weaker in quiet dealings Monday compared
with that last Friday.
</P>
<P>
Traders said the weak Japanese yen was the main factor that
caused investors to dump shares.
</P>
<P>
Bank shares fell to fresh year lows on renewed pessimism over
the economy and rising interest rates.
</P>
<P>
Total market volume fell to 119.49 million units, valued at
248.88 million Singapore dollars (142.22 million U.S. dollars).
There were 29 rises against 313 falls while 248 other counters
remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Easyknit remained the most actively traded stock as it
registered a turnover of 11.60 million units. It was followed by
ST Engg which had 6.78 million shares traded. SingTel was next
with 6.26 million shares changing hands.
</P>
<P>
Creative 50 topped the gainers list of the day as it rose by
0.60 Singapore dollars to finish at 21.50 Singapore dollars.
Jurship increased by 35 cents to end at 8.00 Singapore dollars.
Pelangi was up by 13.6 cents to close at o.61 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Rothmans was the biggest loser as it shed 70
cents to end at 11.00 Singapore dollars. UOB F lost 55 cents to
close at 5.05 Singapore dollars. OCBC F was next which fell by 45
cents to finish at 5.45 Singapore dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
