<DOCNO> XIE19980615.0147 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Taxation Administration Vows to Reach Tax Income Target </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 15 (Xinhua) -- Jin Renqing, director of the State
General Administration of Taxation, today urged the national
taxation system to overcome difficulties and reach this year's
target of increasing tax revenue by 80 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Statistics released during today's session of a national
taxation conference show that national industrial and commercial
tax revenue through the end of May stood at 304.57 billion yuan,
(36.7 billion US dollars) up 7.9 percent on last year's same
period. Value-added and consumption tax revenues for the period
grew by one percent to 151.78 billion yuan (18.3 billion US
dollars). However, both figures failed to achieve the planned
growth rate.
</P>
<P>
Jin said that the major factors accounting for slower than
expected growth included the impact of Asian financial crisis, the
declining efficiency of state-owned enterprises and the slow
growth rate for exports.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, Jin urged the national taxation system to accelerate
taxation efforts by reducing tax arrears, strengthening tax audits
and introducing strong punishment for tax evasion.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
