<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Blatter Says World Cup Start "Storming" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
PARIS, June 15 (Xinhua) -- FIFA President Joseph Sepp Blatter
held a press conference after Croatia-Jamaica match later on Sunday
night and praised the "storming start" of the World Cup finals.
</P>
<P>
Blatter said:"The game is in good shape. I have rarely known such
a storming start to a World Cup, with such attractive football. I've
always said that with thirt-two teams in the final competition, teams
will have to play to win, and not simply to avoid losing."
</P>
<P>
"The players as a whole are disciplined and the referees'
performance has been good up to now. I have no other adjective to
add for the moment." Blatter said.
</P>
<P>
As a response to the statements of French President Jacques
Chirac who said on Sunday that FIFA was entirely respenisble for the
ticketing situation, Blatter said:"It is not for me to comment on
the statements of Jacques Chirac. It is the joint responsibility of
FIFA and the French Organising Committee. We must learn from this
situation and make sure that it never happens again. It is not
solely the problem of football, it is a global problem." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
