<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Norway, Scotland to Play Crucial Group Match </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
BORDEAUX, June 15 (Xinhua) -- Norway and Scotland will play
their second group match on Tuesday with both teams needing to win.
</P>
<P>
The Norway-Scotland match will open the second round of the
group competitions and the World Cup pressure mounts.
</P>
<P>
As Norway will play their last group match against Brazil, so
they needs a victory against Scotland to have any chance of
progressing past the first round for the first time. Only the top
two teams from each group qualify for the knock-out stage.
</P>
<P>
And if Scotland lose the match, they will become the first team
to be out of the World Cup finals.
</P>
<P>
Scotland coach Craig Brown knows that his team have the ability to
beat either Norway or Morocco. If they can win the two matches, the
Scottish team will ensure a passage to the second round despite
skipper Gary McAllister being ruled out of World Cup finals due to
injury.
</P>
<P>
In a bid to turn things around, Brown is likely to replace
Darren Jackson with either Craig Burley or Billy McKinlay.
</P>
<P>
"I will certainly think about adjusting tactically for the next
game and we may also look at changing the personnel."
</P>
<P>
Norway coach Egil Olsen said he would not change his
tactics:"Maybe our style evolves around a lot of high balls and
set-pieces, but that won't change against Scotland."
</P>
<P>
Norway have remained unbeaten for 17 months. The Norwegian
public are expecting their team to go beyond the first round for the
first time in three World Cup finals.
</P>
<P>
Midfielder Oyvind Leonhardsen, who plays for England club
Liverpool, said he expected a much-improved performance compared to
the Morocco match.
</P>
<P>
"I think we are all a bit relaxed now. We've got our first match
out of the way. We know we can do a lot better than we did against
Morocco." said Leonhardsen.
</P>
<P>
The Norway-Scotland match will be played at Bordeaux on Tuesday.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
