<HEADLINE> English Fans to be Directly Sent to Stadium </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MARSEILLE, June 15 (Xinhua) -- English fans arriving at the local
airport here will be sent directly to an area near the Stade Velodrome
for a World Cup here later on Monday.
</P>
<P>
From there some of them could enter the stadium but security
concerning those ticketless remains a headache for the local
authorities.
</P>
<P>
Sporadic skirmishes took place for two consecutive days between the
English and Tunisian fans since Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Dozens of fans have been arrested and at least two Englishmen were
hospitalized for serious wounds.
</P>
<P>
Local police has tightened the security in the area with deployment
of about 2,000 officers and a 100-men special anti-riot force. 
</P>
</TEXT>
