<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Forces Continue Advancing Northwards </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, June 15 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan government troops
continued advancing northwards from their earlier held positions
in general area Mankulam in the Northern province of the island
nation, a military spokesman said Monday.
</P>
<P>
He said the Tamil rebels fired small arms and mortars at
advancing troops. The troops backed by armor destroyed a portion
of the rebel defenses and captured rebel-held areas east of
Mankulam town causing heavy casualties to the rebels. They fled
further northward with their casualties.
</P>
<P>
Another column of troops moving northward captured an important
 rebel stronghold west of Mankulam town Sunday evening. M1-24
helicopters of the air force effectively supported the advancing
troops, spokesman Ink Dewage said.
</P>
<P>
During the day troops engaged and killed five rebels northeast
of Mankulam town. At present, strategically important Mankulam
junction is virtually surrounded by the troops, said Dewage,
adding that the Tamil rebels are in disarray due to their
inability to repel the attacks by the advancing troops and
continue to hold onto Mankulam junction.
</P>
<P>
The fighting took place after the troops continued their
advance to recapture the strategic Mankulam town on its way to
clear a 75-km route between the South and the North launched in
May last year.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels are fighting for a separate state homeland for
 minority Tamils in Sri Lanka's north and east in a war which
began in 1983. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980615.0161 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Newcastle Vaccination Drive Launched in Zimbabwe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, June 15 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe Monday has started a
nationwide Newcastle disease vaccination campaign for over one
year for mainly chickens and ostriches, the daily Herald reported
Monday.
</P>
<P>
Minister of Lands and Agriculture Kumbirai Kangai Sunday
received 15 million doses of V4 Newcastle disease vaccine to be
used in the exercise from the United Nations Food and Agriculture
Organization.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a handing-over ceremony here, Kangai was happy
that people in communal areas who depend most on poultry for food
would benefit from the free campaign.
</P>
<P>
Ostrich meat exports to Europe and other developed countries
are threatened by the presence of Newcastle disease, he said.
</P>
<P>
He noted that it is important that the virus is eradicated if
exports are to be protected especially at a time when the new
ostrich industry is now earning valuable foreign currency for the
country.
</P>
<P>
Newcastle disease is contagious and affects birds. Almost all
poultry exposed to the virus die from the disease. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
