<HEADLINE> Harbin Trade Fair Invites Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, June 15 (Xinhua) -- The Ninth Harbin Trade Fair, which
opened today in northeast China's Heilongjiang Province, features
1,078 enterprises seeking investments from both at home and abroad.
</P>
<P>
Heilongjiang Deputy Governor Zhang Chengyi said interested
investors will be encouraged to cooperate with local companies in
such forms as reorganization, mergers, takeovers, leases,
contracts, shareholding and outright purchases.
</P>
<P>
The list includes 718 state-owned enterprises, 306 collective
companies and 54 private companies and joint ventures.
</P>
<P>
Sixty percent of the enterprises offer expansive markets and
good potential. The enterprises have total assets of 20.03 billion
yuan and mainly come from the light industry, machine-building,
building materials, textile and grain sectors.  
</P>
</TEXT>
