<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Economic, Trade Ties Offer Opportunities, Challenges  (4) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Zeng noted that China has urged the U.S. government to ease
technical export limitations on China and remove barriers such as
the annual review of China's Most Favored Nation status and entry
into the World Trade Organization.
</P>
<P>
Limitations on high-tech exports will weaken the competitive
edge of U.S. enterprises, said Zeng. For example, U.S. nuclear
energy enterprises failed to get "major opportunities" to
participate in China's nuclear power development program due to
the delayed congressional approval of the Sino-U.S. Agreement on
the Peaceful Use of Nuclear Power which the two governments signed
early in 1985.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, he added, "the conservative attitude of American
financial institutions has created unfavorable fund-raising
conditions which have prevented certain American power generation
equipment producers from bidding on highly profitable contract."
</P>
<P>
Zeng went on to say that bilateral cooperation in many fields
will have room for further expansion in the future. "In additon to
promoting cooperation between large enterprises, the two
governments should enage in special efforts to create beneficial
conditions and provide assistance to promote cooperation between
small- to medium-sized enterprises," according to Zeng. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980615.0166 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-15 08:43 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Israeli-Turkish Ties Not Directed At </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, June 15 (Xinhua) -- Israeli Ambassador to Turkey Uri
Bar-Ner has denied that the Israeli-Turkish military cooperation
is directed at Syria, a foe of both countries.
</P>
<P>
In an exclusive interview with Turkish Daily News, which was
published Monday, Bar-Ner said that this cooperation does not
constitute a threat to Syria.
</P>
<P>
"We are not going to fight with Turkey against Syria, and
Turkey is not going to fight with Israel against Syria," Bar-Ner
said.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the Turco-Israeli military cooperation was aimed
at creating a peaceful environment for themselves and the Middle
East as well.
</P>
<P>
"What it (the Israeli-Turkish cooperation) will do will be to
tell Syria that it has to seek peace and stop supporting
terrorism," said the Israeli ambassador.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, he admitted that Israel and Turkey, which have big
defense establishments in the region, are joining together to
"work with the whole interest of creating a deterrent."
</P>
<P>
Israel and Turkey both share bitter relations with Damascus
due to various reasons and they accuse Syria of supporting
terrorist activities.
</P>
<P>
Bar-Ner declined to comment on whether Jordan, an Arab country,
is participating the Turkish-Israeli military cooperation.
</P>
<P>
There were reports that Jordian pilots would receive training
in Turkey as Turkish pilots went to Israel for flight practices.
</P>
<P>
"They feel that Israel, Turkey and Jordan are working
together. I hope it will eventually be more in the economic field
than anything else," Bar-Ner said.
</P>
<P>
Israel and Turkey have signed a series of military and defense
accords under which they share airspace and bases for training
purposes.
</P>
<P>
The rapidly expanding Turkish-Israeli military cooperation has
prompted serious concern among Arab countries who fear it would
change the region's balance of power.
</P>
<P>
Some Arab states also feel restless about Jordan's closer
ties with Turkey and Israel. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
