<HEADLINE> Philippine Peso Plunges Against U.S. Dollar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 15 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine currency peso Monday
fell sharply against the U.S. dollar as a result of the continued
weakness of the Japanese yen.
</P>
<P>
The peso plunged to a four-month low of 42.55 pesos a dollar to
close the day's trading, down by 5.7 percent from last Thursday's
trading.
</P>
<P>
Analysts and dealers said the weaker yen aroused fears of
another round of financial crisis in Asia and raised the spector
that the regional economy would contract further.
</P>
<P>
At press time, the yen fell to 146.27 yen per dollar, the
lowest in eight years.
</P>
<P>
The sentiment also sent the Philippine stock market into
turmoil, driving the composite index of the Philippine Stock
Exchange to drop 82 points to a record low of 1,746,86 points in
recent months. 
</P>
</TEXT>
