<HEADLINE> Harbin Trade Fair Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, June 15 (Xinhua) -- The Ninth Harbin Trade Fair opened
today in Harbin, capital of northeast China's Heilongjiang Province.
</P>
<P>
The seven-day event, the largest fair over the past eight
years, has attracted some 1,200 firms from 10 countries and
regions.
</P>
<P>
This year's commodities exhibition hall offers 20,000 product
varieties in twenty categories.
</P>
<P>
The event will also feature a series activities which will
include seminars on international trade and technical cooperation
and trade negotiations
</P>
<P>
The fair, an event sponsored by local governments, has grown
into one of China's of the seven largest regional trade
fairs. Related activities have promoted cooperation between
Chinese and foreign firms, especially firms from countries in the
Commonwealth of Independent States.
</P>
<P>
The eighth fair yielded investments valued at 3.4 billion
U.S. dollars, including trade agreements valued at 1.8 billion US
dollar and technical cooperation agreements worth 1.2 billion U.S.
dollars. 
</P>
