<P>
Barak arrived here Monday morning and was greeted upon arrival
by Egyptian Deputy Prime Minister and Minister of Agriculture,
Animal and Pisciculture and Land Reclamation Youssef Wali.
</P>
<P>
His visit to Cairo comes in the wake of a visit paid to Cairo a
few days ago by Israeli Defense Minister Yitzhak Mordechai and his
meeting with Mubarak to discuss means of activating the peace
process on the Palestinian track.
</P>
<P>
Palestinian-Israeli talks came to a halt in March 1997 when
Israel started construction of a new Jewish settlement in Arab
East Jerusalem. Palestinian suicide bombings and foot-dragging in
the Israeli troop redeployment in the West Bank have worsened
the crisis.
</P>
<P>
In a related development, a top Labor Party official, Youssi
Belein, arrived here Sunday night for a few hours visit during
which he held talks with Mubarak's political advisor Osama el-Baz
on the peace process impasse. 
</P>
</TEXT>
