<HEADLINE> Philippine MILF Rebels Bomb Military Detachments </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 15 (Xinhua) -- Moro Islamic Liberation Front
(MILF) rebels Monday fired mortar shots at four army detachments
in Buldon, Maguindanao province in the southern Philippines.
</P>
<P>
In a report to the military headquarters, Major General Rolando
Bautista, commander of the Sixth Infantry Division, said the MILF
rebels fired about 15 rounds of 81 mm. mortar fire at the
detachments.
</P>
<P>
The government troops based there retaliated by firing 81 mm.
mortar counter fires at the rebels' position.
</P>
<P>
The exchange of fire ensued for one hour and 45 minutes,
Bautista said, adding that the government troops suffered no
casualty.
</P>
<P>
It was unknown whether there were any casualties on the rebel
side.
</P>
<P>
The MILF is currently the largest rebel group in the
Philippines. Although engaged in low-level peace talks with the
government, it often clashed with government troops. In encounters
early this month, at least 20 rebels were killed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
