<HEADLINE> Sino-British Cooperation on Poverty-Elimination Discussed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 15 (Xinhua) -- China will continue to seek
international cooperation for its poverty-alleviation effort, a
senior Chinese official said here today.
</P>
<P>
Britain has provided China with donation and loans, and the two
countries have conducted good cooperation in China's poverty
alleviation endeavor, said Vice-Minister of Foreign Trade and
Economic Cooperation Sun Zhenyu during his talks with British
Secretary of State for International Development Clare Short.
</P>
<P>
Sun said that the mixture of donation and loans has been used
in China's 40-plus projects for poverty-alleviation.
</P>
<P>
The new British government changed its cooperation policy with
China by mainly providing it with donations rather than mixture of
loans, he noted, and the Chinese government respects this policy
change.
</P>
<P>
Sun expressed his hope that new cooperative projects and
related measures between the two countries will be implemented at
an earlier date.
</P>
<P>
Short said the policy change of her government is aimed at more
effective use of Britain's assistance to China, and that the
amount of the fund will not be reduced.
</P>
<P>
The British government hopes that the fund will be used in the
areas of environmental protection, health care, the reform of
primary education and China's state-owned enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Short and her party are currently on a visit to China at the
invitation of Chinese Minister of Foreign Trade and Economic
Cooperation Shi Guangsheng.  
</P>
</TEXT>
