<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hunan Expands Use of Farm Machinery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, June 15 (Xinhua) -- Hunan Province, a major grain
production base in central China, has extended great effort to
ensure the effective use of farm machinery.
</P>
<P>
The province has introduced some 115,000 pieces of farm
machinery annually since 1993. Hunan's farm machinery has a total
capacity of 16.9 million kilowatts.
</P>
<P>
This summer's demand for small combines, a relatively expensive
piece of farm machinery priced at 12,000 yuan, has far outstripped
supply. Brisk sales have also been recorded for machinery such as
seeders, transport vehicles and irrigation and drainage
equipment.
</P>
<P>
Latest statistics show the province achieved a 64 percent
mechanization rate for 1997 and projections call for farm
machinery to be used on 2.8 million ha in 1998, up 200,000 ha on
the previous year.
</P>
<P>
The number of individuals purchasing farm machinery continues to
grow and agricultural service companies have emerged as a major
consumer force. Related companies operate large fleets of farm
machinery and routinely contract irrigation and drainage projects
for farmers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980615.0198 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-15 </DATE_TIME>
