<BODY>
<HEADLINE> India's Cyclone Toll Reaches 1,051 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 15 (Xinhua) -- The toll of India's recent
cyclone storm hitting the states of Gujarat, Maharashtra and
Rajasthan has reached 1,051 with the recovery of some more bodies
from these three states, official sources said here Monday.
</P>
<P>
The cyclone storm started on June 9 and the worse hit area was
Kandla-Kutch of Gujarat State of southwestern India, which has
witnessed 794 deaths so far.
</P>
<P>
Unofficial figure of death, however, has been put at 2,200. As
many as 40 heath teams have been working in Kutch district to
prevent the outbreak of any epidemic, the very fear of which has
caused an exodus from Kandla and its surrounding areas. Over 4,800
people are being treated for various ailments and 2,189 injured
people are also under treatment.
</P>
<P>
At least 2,338 villages are still without power and six major
roads connecting major districts remain unmotorable because of the
severe damage caused by the last Tuesday's cyclone, the same
sources said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
