<HEADLINE> U.S. Asked Not to Interfere in Indonesia's  Domestic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, June 15 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian legislators have asked
the United States to ensure that American aid is not used to
finance activities which would interfere in the country's domestic
affairs, The Jakarta Post reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
Six legislators delivered two letters, one addressed to U.S.
President Bill Clinton and the other to U.S. Congress, to U.S.
Ambassador J. Stapleton Roy here Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The two letters were signed by 89 members of the 500-member
House of Representatives.
</P>
<P>
