<HEADLINE> U.S. Brokered-Moratorium Accepted by Ethiopia, Eritrea </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 14 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia and Eritrea have
accepted a U.S. brokered moratorium on air strike, announced the
government of the United States Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The governments of Eritrea and Ethiopia, in response to a
U.S. proposal, have agreed to halt immediately air strikes and
threat of air strikes in their border conflict, White House
spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
The moratorium will continue indefinitely, unless both parties
"conclude that any prospect for a peace process has come to an
end", and provide in advance formal notice to the U.S. government
to terminate the moratorium. said the spokesman.
</P>
<P>
U.S. President Bill Clinton talked with leaders of both
countries on telephone Sunday before the moratorium was reached,
reports said.
</P>
<P>
Eritrea was ready, said its government on Sunday, to have
face-to-face talks with Ethiopia to solve the border conflict
peacefully. The border conflict has claimed lives of hundreds
victims. 
</P>
