<HEADLINE> Shanxi Improves Safety in State Coal Mines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, June 15 (Xinhua) -- Shanxi Province, China's leading
coal producer, has significantly improved safety in major
state-owned coal mines in the first four months of the year.
</P>
<P>
According to the Provincial Coal Industry Department, the
overall mortality rate for that period plummeted by 91 percent to
an all-time low of 0.05 per person for every one million tons
mined.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang Zemin praised the achievement in a letter to
the director of the Provincial Coal Industry Department. "Continue
your effort and do a better job in both production and safety in
operation."
</P>
<P>
Shanxi produces an average 340 million tons of coal annually,
about a quarter of China's total. It suspended production during
February celebrations of the Spring Festival, the traditional
period for celebrating Chinese Lunar New Year, to conduct a
comprehensive inspection of safety measures and eliminate safety
hazards. 
</P>
