<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fujian Expands Cooperation With Taiwan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, June 15 (Xinhua) -- Meteorologists from eastern
China's Fujian Province and Taiwan has initiated a joint research
project to forecast typhoons and torrential rains which commonly
hit areas near the Taiwan Straits.
</P>
<P>
Meteorologists from Fujian and Taiwan have engaged in extensive
academic exchanges to study torrential rains in the Taiwan region,
the establishment of an experimental early warning system in
southern China.
</P>
<P>
Fujian introduced typhoon warnings for Taiwan April 14, 1972,
with weather forecasts over the past 26 years representing an
important basis for the farming sector and fisheries on both sides
of the Taiwan Straits.
</P>
<P>
In 1992, meteorologists from Fujian and Taiwan expanded
cooperation from simply exchanges of meteorological information in
the form of publications, letters and facsimiles to direct
telephone contacts concerning weather forecasting and meetings
attended by experts in the field. 
</P>
</TEXT>
