<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guangxi Reinforces Science and Technology </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, June 15 (Xinhua) -- South China's Guangxi Zhuang
Autonomous Region has substantially increased funding to reinforce
science and technology in recent years.
</P>
<P>
A regional government official said the combination of
government allocations and non-governmental inputs has resulted in
a substantial influx of funding for science and technology.
</P>
<P>
Local governments at all levels alone have allocated some one
billion yuan for science and technology since 1990, with the
average annual increase standing at 18.52 percent.
</P>
<P>
Close to six billion yuan has been used for science and
technology activities since 1990, up 26.85 percent on an annual
basis. Three billion yuan has been used to develop technology for
medium- and large-sized enterprises, with related funding rising by
36.36 percent annually.
</P>
<P>
The region used loans totalling 658 million yuan to support
science and technology projects between 1995-1997, with an
additional 58 million yuan used for related development efforts.
</P>
<P>
Fifteen cities and 80 counties in Guangxi have established
science and technology funds totalling 37 million yuan.
</P>
</TEXT>
