<HEADLINE>   Clinton's China Visit to Contribute to Regional </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, June 15 (Xinhua) -- A senior official of the
Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) expressed the hope
that U.S. President Bill Clinton's forthcoming visit to China will
contribute to the regional stability.
</P>
<P>
In an exclusive interview with Xinhua here recently, ASEAN
Secretary General Rodolfo C. Severino pointed out that the visit
by the U.S. president to China is a good thing.
</P>
<P>
In this time of economic globalization and financial crisis, it
is good for the world that the most powerful economy and the
biggest developing country get together and have an understanding
of what is required by both the developed and developing countries
in overcoming this crisis, he said.
</P>
<P>
He believed that the visit could strengthen relations between
China and the U.S.
</P>
<P>
"Good relations between China and the U.S. are good for the
international community and for regional stability. So I think
that this kind of inter-action, this kind of relationship should
be increased," Severino said.
</P>
<P>
Answering a question about the role China and the U.S. have
played and should play in the international arena, Severino was
glad to see that both China and the U.S. participated in the ASEAN
Regional Forum (ARF), established in July 1994 on the initiative
of ASEAN.
</P>
<P>
ASEAN invites foreign ministers from China, the U.S., the
European Union, Japan, South Korea, Australia, New Zealand,
Canada, Russia, Papua New Guinea, Laos and Cambodia to discuss
political issues and security situation in the Asia Pacific area
under the ARF annually.
</P>
<P>
The ASEAN secretary general stressed that ASEAN has taken the
lead in organizing the ARF.
</P>
<P>
"And in that way, all the participants in the ARF have a better
understanding of what's China position and what's U.S. position,"
the General Secretary said, adding that he hoped China and the
U.S. have better understanding of each other's position.
</P>
<P>
AS an important regional organization, ASEAN has played a very
significant role in maintaining peace and stability in the region
as well as economic development and cooperation.
</P>
<P>
"In order to continue to play that role, ASEAN must move
forward on its own solidarity, it's activity in the world
affairs," Severino explained.
</P>
<P>
On the China-ASEAN relations, the secretary general said that
ASEAN has very good relations both with the U.S. and China.
</P>
<P>
Recalling the ASEAN-China senior officials' consultations held
in April this year, he said the consultations which he attended
"are very good because the best yield has seen."
</P>
<P>
If ASEAN and China keep it up and refrain from acts that would
harm the security of each other, "ASEAN-China relations will keep
growing in the future for the benefit of both," Severino
concluded. 
</P>
</TEXT>
