<HEADLINE> Hainan Province Develops Gas Resources </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, June 15 (Xinhua) -- Hainan, China's southernmost island
province, is making full use of its abundant offshore natural gas
resources to develop environment-friendly projects.
</P>
<P>
The Haikou Gas Pipeline Company in this capital of Hainan
Province helped the local bus company convert 35 buses from
gasoline to natural gas. The conversion effectively reduced
vehicle emissions by 30 percent, with considerable reductions in
discharges of carbon monoxide, hydrocarbon and various other
pollutants.
</P>
<P>
The project also reduced pollution factors such as engine
temperatures and noise levels, while at the same time reducing
fuel costs by 20 yuan per kilometer.
</P>
<P>
The gas company has also developed natural gas systems for air
conditioners and street lights. When compared to freon, natural
gas costs less and creates no harm to the ozone layer. The
province's new government office building will be equipped with
the new air conditioners. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
