<HEADLINE> Rongcheng Becomes Major Sea Products Base </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, June 15 (Xinhua) -- Rongcheng in east China's Shandong
Province has emerged as the nation's major production base for
precious sea products, with the annual output of related products
standing at 380,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
The city's 30,000 hectare aquaculture production area offers
rich fishing grounds for abalone and shellfish. Rongcheng has
established 18 onshore sea products farms and 34 abalone farms.
</P>
<P>
The rapid development of sea aquaculture and foreign trade has
transformed Rongcheng into a booming coastal city.
</P>
<P>
The local government has developed deep-sea and land-based
aquaculture in addition to offshore operations.
</P>
<P>
Artificial breeding, a practice formerly limited to kelp, has
been introduced to 30 varieties. The city has also introduced new
fish varieties from the United States and Japan.  
</P>
</TEXT>
