<HEADLINE> Jiangsu Proposes Projects For Overseas Investors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 15 (Xinhua) -- A package of 40 projects to be
carried out in Yangzhou, in east China's Jiangsu Province, have
been announced here to invite overseas investment totalling more
than 2.1 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Of the projects, six deal with infrastructure construction, 22
involve the industrial sector, six are in agriculture and six are
in the service sector.
</P>
<P>
Twenty-nine projects require more than 10 million US dollars
each, and two need more than 30 million US dollars each.
</P>
<P>
The second phase of construction of the No. 2 Power Plant in
Yangzhou, which is believed to be the largest project in the city,
will cost 830 million US dollars and will have two 600,000-kw
coal-fueled generating units.
</P>
<P>
The second-largest project is a 5,600-m-long bridge with six
traffic lanes linking Yangzhou with the neighboring city of
Zhenjiang, which will involve 550 million US dollars in
investment.  
</P>
