<BODY>
<HEADLINE> State to Curb Drain of Capital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 15 (Xinhua) -- The central government is expected
to take measures to curb capital drain from collectively-owned
township enterprises in their structural reform, according to an
official with the Ministry of Agriculture.
</P>
<P>
He was quoted on the front page of today's China Daily as
saying that the ministry has submitted a draft to the Central
Committee of the Communist Party of China and the State Council,
which are to issue a joint circular on the issue.
</P>
<P>
Collective firms' capital drain, evasion of bank debts, and
their stereotyped reform procedure have been the widespread
problems in the reform drive, said Vice-Minister Qi Jingfa.
</P>
<P>
He noted there are reports saying collective township
enterprises have been sold to individuals at prices much lower
than their real value. "While not wholly true, it has become the
current trend."
</P>
<P>
According to the Vice-Minister, the circular to be issued is
expected to urge local authorities not to register township
enterprises whose ownership is disputed as individual private
business. Any such registration in the past should be corrected.
</P>
<P>
All township authorities are expected to record the collective
capital of enterprises and introduce complete management and
auditing regulation.
</P>
<P>
Qi said that the collective fund, acquired by selling firms or
shares, should not be spent on non-productive issues, or
squandered. And the enterprises should not be interfered by
governments on their decision making.
</P>
<P>
A central government circular issued on Thursday requires
creditor banks to take part in dealing with the debts of firms
undergoing reform in order to prevent them evading their debts.
</P>
<P>
Some 520,000 rural collective enterprises in China, one third
of the total, had been sold, annexed, declared bankrupt or
transformed into shareholding co-operative companies by the end of
last year, according to Jiang Yongtao, director of the ministry's
Township Enterprise Bureau.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
