<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Research Project Launched in Huaihe River Valley </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, June 15 (Xinhua) -- China and Japan have jointly
launched a program to study climatic conditions in the Huaihe
River Valley.
</P>
<P>
The "Center for Studying Energy and Water Cycles in the Huaihe
River Valley" was recently established at the Anhui Provincial
Meteorological Bureau.
</P>
<P>
Related experiments will focus on studying the causes of
drought and flooding in the river valley, with meteorological and
hydrological observations expected to improve forecasting
capabilities.
</P>
<P>
The experimental area covers a total of 16 provinces and cities
in the river valley. 
</P>
</TEXT>
