<HEADLINE> Alonso Wins Bologna Tennis Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, June 14 (Xinhua) -- Third seed Julian Alonso of Spain won
the second title of his career when he defeated 6th seed Moroccan
Karim Alami in two straight sets to win the men's clay court
tournament in Bologna, Italy on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The world number 39 spent less than an hour to edge his rival
6-1, 6-4.
</P>
<P>
It was 20-year-old Alonso's first title since he beat current
world number two Marcelo Rios in his hometown Santiago last
October.
</P>
<P>
Alonso did not drop a set all week, showing his good form which
last year saw him climb 253 ranking spots into the world's top
50. 
