<HEADLINE> Several Injured in JAL Plane Accident in Manila </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 15 (Xinhua) -- Several passengers were slightly
injured when a Japan Airlines plane swerved off the runway while
landing at the Manila's international airport Sunday night.
</P>
<P>
The Philippine Newspaper "Manila Bulletin" reported Monday that
the airport was temporarily closed because the plane blocked the
tarmac as its wheels became stuck in the mud after landing.
</P>
<P>
Several passengers were injured while being evacuated from the
MD-11 plane, it said.
</P>
<P>
The paper said that the plane, flight JL 745 from Tokyo, was
making its second landing approach when the accident occurred.
</P>
<P>
The pilot was apprehensive because of limited visibility during
the first approach caused by an earlier storm, it said. 
</P>
