<HEADLINE> Salas Sustains Thigh Strain in Training </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
BORDEAUX, June 14 (Xinhua) -- Chilean striker Marcelo Salas
sustained a thigh strain during a training match on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Salas, who scored twice in Chile's first group match against
Italy, said he should be fit again in a couple of days.
</P>
<P>
Salas played only five minutes of the training game before he
sustained the injury.
</P>
<P>
"It was just a contraction of the muscle so I hope to be better
over the next two days." Salas said.
</P>
<P>
"If I take some medication and get some rest I should get over
it." said Salas.
</P>
<P>
Chile will take on Austria on Wednesday in their second Group B
match. 
</P>
</TEXT>
