<HEADLINE> Argentina Still Has Room to Improve: Captain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOULOUSE, June 14 (Xinhua) -- Argentine captain Diego Simeone said
his side still has room to improve after the team's 1-0 victory over
Japan here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
"We have to feel quite satisfied, but of couse we can also improve
and we will improve," said Simeone.
</P>
<P>
He added, "We don't fear anyone in the group. Now we are just going
to settle down and relax before the game with Jamaica."
</P>
<P>
Argentina's coach Daniel Passarella said he was more than satisfied
with the result as "it is alway difficult to win the first match of a
World Cup."
</P>
<P>
Argentina had been beaten in 1990 World Cup finals by Cameroon in
their first group match. 
</P>
</TEXT>
