<DOCNO> XIE19980615.0260 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zagallo Punctures Brazilian Team's Peak Time </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
PARIS, June 14 (Xinhua) -- Brazilian head coach Mario Zagallo
said his team would peak at the World Cup finals when it matters most.
</P>
<P>
Zagallo said at the Brazilian in Ozoir-La-Ferriere that he saw
clear signs in Sunday's training that his team was improving
steadily.
</P>
<P>
Zagallo said Brazilian poor performances in some of the warm-up
matches were nothing to worry about:"Everything is getting better.
If you reach your peak before the competition starts, then you have
nowhere left to go."
</P>
<P>
"The only way for us to go is up. We are improving each day and
today's training showed this. It's always good to know that you can
produce more." said Zagallo.
</P>
<P>
Zagallo said:"If you get to the top too soon, it's easier to go
down again than to try and maintain the same level."
</P>
<P>
Zagallo rejected the suggestions his remarks about peaking so soon
were aimed at Argentina. The Argentine team played superbly in their
warm-up matches but had a difficult time in the match against Japan.
</P>
<P>
"I really don't want to talk about other teams. Everyone talk
about Brazil but I don't speak about the others." Zagallo said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
